      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>crushed garlic</strong>, <strong>onion wedges </strong>and <strong>carrot discs </strong>to the dish with 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp] </span><strong>flour </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper </strong>and cook for 1-2 min</p><p>Add 600ml<span class=\"text-purple\"><span class=\"text-danger\"> [750ml] </span>[900ml] </span><strong>boiled water</strong> to the dish with your <strong>bay leaf[ves]</strong>,<strong> tomato paste</strong>, <strong>marmite</strong> and <strong>beef stock mix</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, cover with a lid, then put the dish in the oven for an initial 30 min</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1718367665514-x200.jpg",
